table abc_extra201.register_defaults_and_abcmeta_identity:
  description: "abc.ABCMeta.register __defaults__ and ABCMeta class identity checks in abcdefaults201 namespace — register.__defaults__ is None (NoneType) because register(cls, subclass) takes two required arguments; ABCMeta.__class__.__name__=='type' (ABCMeta is a metaclass — its own type is 'type'); ABCMeta.__name__=='ABCMeta' (len=7: A-B-C-M-e-t-a); ABC.__class__.__name__=='ABCMeta' (ABC is an instance of ABCMeta — a class created with ABCMeta as its metaclass); verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
